<item>
            <title>[CXF-7799] Query parameters are not handled properly when WebSocket transport is used</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7799</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m trying to pass query parameters to REST endpoint over Websocket transport. I expect the passed parameters to come as query string but instead of this I receive them in the&#160;path.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suppose that there is an issue with Atmosphere that causes it not to pass query parameters to AtmosphereRequest.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Request example (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cxf/tree/master/distribution/src/main/release/samples/jax_rs/websocket&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;JAX-RS WebSocket Demo&lt;/a&gt;):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;GET /demo/customerservice/customers/123?param=value&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected: &quot;123&quot; is passed as a path parameter value&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Actual: value is &quot;123?param=value&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
